Sure, here are some examples:

1. *Smiješ* se cijeli dan. (You are smiling all day.)
2. Da li ti *smiješ* da mi pomogneš oko ovoga? (Are you allowed to help me with this?)
3. Ja *smijem* piti samo jednu čašu vina. (I am allowed to drink only one glass of wine.)
4. *Smijem* se svaki put kad se sjetim te priče. (I laugh every time I remember that story.)
5. Ti se nikada ne *smiješ* mojim šalama. (You never laugh at my jokes.)
6. Kada bih *smio* birati, izabrao bih ovaj restoran. (If I were allowed to choose, I would choose this restaurant.)
7. *Smijemo* se zajedno već satima. (We have been laughing together for hours.)
8. Oni se *smiju* mom glupom ponašanju. (They are laughing at my silly behavior.)
9. Da li *smijem* pitati zašto si to uradio? (May I ask why you did that?)
10. *Smiju li* se djeca u ovoj biblioteci? (Are children allowed to laugh in this library?)

Note: The word "smiješ" is the second person singular form of the verb "smijati se", which means "to laugh" or "to smile". Other forms of this verb used in these sentences include "smijem" (first person singular), "smijemo" (first person plural), and "smiju" (third person plural).